Volume based metastatic spread Metastatic seeding is an exceedingly complex process involving many different steps (Arvelo et al. 2016) and successful formation of metastasis depends on various not yet completely understood biochemical and genetic determinants that require research on their own (Hanahan 2011). As the number of cells which can leave the primary tumour to form metastasis depends on the size of the tumour, Bartoszynski et al. (2001) proposed as a first model the intensity \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
