To study the capabilities of the model to describe real-world observational data, we consider the ACT2-trial (Hagman et al. 2016). In this trial, colorectal cancer patients with KRAS mutations were treated with ACT2. The dataset has been published Cancertrials.io (2022) and was previously fitted with a Weibull distribution Plana et al. (2022). The Gompertz growth based model was able to mimick the survival curve of this trial as shown in Fig. 4. MLE-based distribution fitting showed that a Gompertz distribution with parameters \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
